Real Analysis & Measure Theory

Bolzano–Weierstrass Theorem

Every bounded sequence in \mathbb{R}^n has a convergent subsequence.

Heine–Borel Theorem

A subset of \mathbb{R}^n is compact iff it is closed and bounded.

Cantor Set

C = [0,1]\setminus\bigcup_n\bigcup_k (\text{removed middle thirds})


The Cantor set is uncountable, has Lebesgue measure zero, and is nowhere dense.

Monotone Convergence Theorem

If f_n \uparrow f pointwise and f_n\ge 0, then \int f_n \to \int f.

Fatou’s Lemma

\int\liminf f_n \le \liminf\int f_n

A cornerstone of Lebesgue integration theory.

Dominated Convergence Theorem

If f_n\to f pointwise and |f_n|\le g with g\in L^1, then \int f_n \to \int f.

Tonelli / Fubini Theorems

For non‑negative or absolutely integrable functions, the double integral equals the iterated integral in either order: \iint f(x,y)\,dx\,dy = \int\!\int f\,dx\,dy.

Hölder Inequality

\int|fg| \le \|f\|_p\,\|g\|_q,\qquad \frac{1}{p}+\frac{1}{q}=1

Generalizes Cauchy–Schwarz (p=q=2).

Minkowski Inequality

\|f+g\|_p \le \|f\|_p + \|g\|_p

This is the triangle inequality in L^p spaces.

L^p Spaces

L^p = \{f : \int|f|^p < \infty\},\qquad \|f\|_p = \left(\int|f|^p\right)^{1/p}

Banach spaces are complete normed vector spaces (L^p spaces are Banach).

Hilbert Space

A complete inner‑product space. L^2 is the prototypical Hilbert space. The Riesz representation theorem states that every bounded linear functional on a Hilbert space is given by an inner product.

Baire Category Theorem

A complete metric space cannot be expressed as a countable union of nowhere‑dense sets.

Uniform Continuity

\forall\varepsilon>0\;\exists\delta>0:\; |x-y|<\delta \Rightarrow |f(x)-f(y)|<\varepsilon \text{ for ALL } x,y

Stronger than pointwise continuity; the same \delta works for every pair of points.

Weierstrass M‑Test

If |f_n(x)|\le M_n and \sum M_n<\infty, then \sum f_n converges uniformly.

Lebesgue Integration

The compendium presents an integral \mathbb{E}[L] = \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{\lambda^k e^{-\lambda}}{k!} f(k) as an illustration of Lebesgue integration ideas.

Measure Spaces

The fundamental framework for modern probability and real analysis.

